## 3. Database Schemas

### Schema Layout

| Schema | Purpose | Managed By |
|--------|---------|------------|
| `raw_jira` | Raw data from Jira (append-only) | dlt |
| `raw_gitlab` | Raw data from GitLab | dlt |
| `clean_jira` | Normalized Jira data | Dagster assets |
| `clean_gitlab` | Normalized GitLab data | Dagster assets |
| `metrics` | Materialized views for BI | SQL views |
| `platform` | Users, integrations, configs | FastAPI/Alembic |

### Initialization

```
db/
├── init/
│   └── 01_create_schemas.sql     # CREATE SCHEMA statements
├── schemas/
│   ├── platform.sql              # Platform tables
│   └── clean_jira.sql            # Clean layer tables
├── views/
│   └── metrics.sql               # Materialized views
└── migrations/
    ├── alembic.ini
    ├── env.py
    └── versions/
```

### Schema Creation (db/init/01_create_schemas.sql)

```sql
-- Create all schemas
CREATE SCHEMA IF NOT EXISTS platform;
CREATE SCHEMA IF NOT EXISTS raw_jira;
CREATE SCHEMA IF NOT EXISTS clean_jira;
CREATE SCHEMA IF NOT EXISTS metrics;

-- Grant permissions
GRANT ALL ON SCHEMA platform TO postgres;
GRANT ALL ON SCHEMA raw_jira TO postgres;
GRANT ALL ON SCHEMA clean_jira TO postgres;
GRANT ALL ON SCHEMA metrics TO postgres;
```

